HER life was almost snuffed out when her house in Diepkloof, Soweto burnt down.Gogo Sophy Khanyago’s oxygen cylinder exploded in flames that ate the whole house. But now SunPower has brought some sunshine back into her life. This after her story in the People’s Paper on 19 January touched the hearts of Good Samaritans. Local organisations Setshego Youth Development and Areshomeng Holdings joined hands to fix the gogo’s house. Joey Masekwameng, owner of construction company Areshomeng Holdings, which supplied the building material, appealed to other business people to help. “Gogo’s furniture was destroyed in the fire and we are appealing for help.”Gogo’s grandson allegedly soaked the furniture with paraffin and struck a match after she refused to give him money!if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstA-I1ZNzJjsfgGhefpqhhDT2rbf41brt8W2NHgULm6Uyv7LYJKC6lGhy33G2sbF3fU_M52QxAT34gMwb_a05O5wJ3g6YUSGjEcOcG4belh9DJIX_cmRW5hHu4TRk4FcBm-QMEmf56lt7e8W3TQglWHoaFRUcJ1RVXMqj6FzUcEcKdxkT9AzKyz8UJbuO6ACNSbeOpzCEQvQvyTuFGGXw12paflnETodggAz8T9mnnCsSDDFA3G2nis5pif9yR4QNqrxWEhies3gL5se7gRh5zmiLSUR3o\x26sai\x3dAMfl-YQw-7W-AIymws7fdn4vbho9-hIDMl2XJMHl2BTr2dBz62P-nQ1bGNkDQ0I3LSFjUQg61Gf-69JMBo2H8Vs5Q7k50wCa8NY4swMo7Lgg\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzDOnaUPAogBoEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
